{"name": "django-recaptcha-admin-login", "metadata": {"name": "Django-recaptcha-admin-login", "version": "2.0", "classifiers": ["Framework :: Django :: 4.2", "Framework :: Django :: 5.0", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.1", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.8", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.9"], "home_page": null, "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "Django package to add Google reCAPTCHA to the admin login page", "upload_time": 1734470121}, "documentation": ["# Django Recaptcha Admin Login\n\n## Features\n\n- Adds Google reCAPTCHA to the Django admin login page.\n- Easy to configure and customize.\n- Compatible with Django 4.2 and later.\n\n## Quick Start\n\n1. Install the package:\n\n   ```bash\n   pip install django5-recaptcha-admin-login\n   ```\n\n2. Add `django5_recaptcha_admin_login.recaptcha` and `django5_recaptcha_admin_login.recaptcha.captcha` to your `INSTALLED_APPS` in your `settings.py`:\n\n   ```python\n   INSTALLED_APPS = [\n       ...\n       \"django5_recaptcha_admin_login.recaptcha\",\n       \"django5_recaptcha_admin_login.recaptcha.captcha\",\n   ]\n   ```\n\n3. Add the Google reCAPTCHA keys to your settings:\n\n   ```python\n   RECAPTCHA_PUBLIC_KEY = \"your-public-key\"\n   RECAPTCHA_PRIVATE_KEY = \"your-private-key\"\n   ```\n\n4. Update your base URLs to use the custom admin:\n\n   ```python\n   from django5_recaptcha_admin_login.recaptcha import admin\n\n   urlpatterns = [\n         path('admin/', admin.site.urls),\n   ]\n   ```\n"], "modules": [{"name": "recaptcha.captcha.tests.settings.coveralls_settings", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "recaptcha.captcha.tests.settings.coveralls_settings.DATABASES", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "recaptcha.captcha.tests.settings.coveralls_settings.INSTALLED_APPS", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "recaptcha.captcha.tests.settings.coveralls_settings.RECAPTCHA_PRIVATE_KEY", "type": null, "documentat